  "response": "For IISER admission through KVPY, the minimum rank requirement varies depending on the stream and the specific IISER. Generally:\n\n1. For KVPY Stream SA (11th standard): Top 300-500 ranks\n\n2. For KVPY Stream SX (12th standard): Top 250-500 ranks\n\n3. Most IISER institutes consider candidates within the top 500 ranks for direct admission.\n\nHowever, the exact cutoff can vary slightly each year based on:\n- Total number of candidates\n- Performance in the KVPY examination\n- Available seats in different IISER campuses\n\nIt's recommended to:\n- Check the current year's specific KVPY and IISER admission guidelines\n- Visit official IISER and KVPY websites for the most up-to-date information\n- Aim for a rank within the top 300-500 for better chances of admission\n\nNote: Meeting the rank criteria doesn't guarantee automatic admission; candidates must also fulfill other eligibility criteria.",
